1. h(左移)     j(下行)     k(上行)     l(右移)

2. enter vim editor,command: vim <filename> <enter>

3. quit: NOT SAVE: ESC-:q!
         SAVE:ESC-:wq

4. delete the charactor: x

5. i: insert before charactor
   a: insert after charactor
   A: insert after line


6. dw:delete a word from pointer
   d$:delete line from pointer
   dd:delete all line
   2dd:delete 2 lines
   2w:move forward 2 words
   3e:move forward to the third word end
   0:move to head of the line
   u:undo
   ctrl-R:undo the undo operation

7. p:put the content deleted behind the cursor   
   r:replace the charactor
   R:replace the charactor consistently
   c:change the content behind the cursor,like ce(word)/c$(line)

8. CTRL-G:show the information of the line pointed by cursor
   G:last line
   gg:first line
   484G:jump to line484 

9. /:search
   ?:search(desc)
   n:next match option
   N:next match option(desc)
   %:find the match bracket
   :s/old/new/g:replace all the old with new of this line
   :1,3s/old/new/g:replace line1 to line3
   :%s/old/new/g:replace in the whole directory
   :%s/old/new/gc:replace in the whole directory,meanwhile,ask u if u want to replace at the same time.
   
10.":!":execute the outdoor command
   ":!ls":show the list of this directory
   ":w FILENAME":write into the file and save
   v:enter the status which can select the content
   ":r FILENAME":read the content of the file
   o:like insert,insert in the line behind the line pointed by cursor
   O:like insert,insert in the line before the line pointed by cursor
   y:copy
   p:taste
   "set ic":ignore case
   "set hls":high line

11.":help: find the help of something
   "CTRL-W CTRL-W": switch the windows
   "edit ~/.vimrc":Unix command, edit the vimrc file
   "edit ~/_vimrc":MS-Windows command, edit the vimrc file   
   "CTRL-D":show all command started by xxx
   "TAB":complete command
   
